        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 30 at 10:47AM EDT by NWS Grand Rapids MI</headline>
        <description>At 1047 AM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Lakeview, or 13 miles northwest of Stanton, moving northeast at 5
mph.

HAZARD...Winds in excess of 40 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Lakeview...            Six Lakes...           Entrican...
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
